Another report claimed yesterday that detectives investigating the death did not find a suicide note.

Some friends continue to insist Mr 
Berezovsky was the victim of a professional hit for speaking out against
Vladimir Putin’s regime. Others believe he killed himself after 
becoming depressed over the loss of his wealth and status.

The mansion in Ascot where he was found is understood to be owned by his former wife Galina Besharova, 54.

Last night her close friend told the 
Mail: ‘Galina is very upset about Boris’s death, as are their children. 
She remained close to Boris after they split up and it was at her house 
that he died.

