‘She really does not want to talk 
about how he died. But there are many ways to induce what may appear to 
be a natural death like a heart attack.’

As speculation raged on  yesterday, an
adviser to Putin even claimed Mr Berezovsky may have been killed by 
British security services.

Using the inflammatory rhetoric of the
Cold War era, Sergei Markov said the tycoon was assassinated because he
knew too much about Western plots to undermine Putin and planned to 
trade this knowledge for a return to Russia.

Mr Markov, a former Russian
politician, said: ‘I cannot say no to the version that it was a murder 
committed by those who were scared Boris Berezovsky would go back to 
Putin’s side.

